            "id": "3f6898b4f8bc4a6c8f700",
            "questionText": "A construction crane lifts a $!$500 \\text{ kg}$!$ steel beam vertically $!$20 \\text{ m}$!$. The lifting force increases linearly from $!$5000 \\text{ N}$!$ at the start to $!$10000 \\text{ N}$!$ at $!$5 \\text{ m}$!$, remains constant at $!$10000 \\text{ N}$!$ from $!$5 \\text{ m}$!$ to $!$15 \\text{ m}$!$, and then decreases linearly back to $!$5000 \\text{ N}$!$ at $!$20 \\text{ m}$!$. Determine the total work done by the crane on the beam during this lift in Joules.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "3d083346fecf4d9e9104f",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula needed to calculate the work done by a force. Please choose the correct formula from the options below.",
